frameDefinitions: This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
This frame contains nouns denoting a rank or level within an established hierarchy.
In this frame either a Stimulus brings about a particular emotion or experience in the Experiencer or  saliently fails to bring about a particular experience.
A Manipulator gets his Victim to perform a Resulting_action against what their better judgment would have been at the time.
An Entity is judged to be sensually pleasing or intellectually interesting to a (generally implicit) Judge.

In this frame an Evaluee is judged by a (usually implicit) Judge to be of a certain character based on her or his Behavior towards other human beings; a specific Affected_party may be overtly mentioned along with the Degree to which the Evaluee behaves appropriately towards others.
frameExamples: Are you trying to tell me that Ace <t>blackmailed</t> you into becoming his lover?
We saw this <t>beautiful</t> boat with the red sails several times
It was <t>nice</t> of you to send a card.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
This role marks expressions that denote a scalar property of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> with respect to which the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged.
The Rank itself, usually denoted by the noun.
An entity which holds a particular <fen>Rank</fen>.
The <fen>Stimulus</fen> is the object or event which brings about the emotion in the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The person who gets the Victim to act against their interest.
The person who the Manipulator gets to do something they would not have done had no pressure or deception been applied.
What the <fen>Manipulator</fen> intends to make the <fen>Victim</fen> do and the <fen>Victim</fen> actually does.
The role goods is anything (including labor, time, or legal rights) that can be taken away.
The time when the manipulation occurs.
The location where the <fen>Manipulator</fen> manipulates the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> for which a particular gradable <fen>Attribute</fen> is appropriate and under consideration.
The feature of an <fen>Entity</fen> which is under discussion.
A modifier expressing    the deviation of the implicit value either from the norm or from the value for another <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having a particular implicit value for the <fen>Attribute</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having a particular implicit value for the <fen>Attribute</fen>.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is the person whose <fen>Behavior</fen> towards other human beings is being evaluated.
The <fen>Affected_party</fen> is the entity which is positively or negatively treated by the <fen>Evaluee</fen>.
The <fen>Behavior</fen> is the action of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> on which the evaluation of the <fen>Evaluee</fen>'s character is based.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the situation or person that the <fen>Evaluee</fen>'s <fen>Behavior</fen> responds to or is related to.
The <fen>Expressor</fen> is the body part or action by a body part which indicates the character of the <fen>Evaluee</fen>.
The individual whose point of view is taken in assigning the evaluation denoted by the target.
listRoleExamples: The Beaujolais Nouveau is dazzling <fex>in freshness</fex>.
Leslie blackmailed <fex>the watch</fex> out of John.
<fex>In my book</fex>, that wasn't very gracious.
